The paper focuses on the development of a novel model for secure cooperation of robotic swarms, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed model also involves the use of cryptographic proofs for data verification, which relates to computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of Merkle trees, a fundamental component of blockchain technology, suggests a potential connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of performance, communication costs, and information diversity requirements suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
